@BankingApp.Api_HostAddress = http://localhost:5242

### List Customers with Pagination
GET {{BankingApp.Api_HostAddress}}/api/customers?pageNumber=1&pageSize=10
Accept: application/json

###

### Get Customer by ID
GET {{BankingApp.Api_HostAddress}}/api/customers/{id}
Accept: application/json

###

### Create Customer
POST {{BankingApp.Api_HostAddress}}/api/customers
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "John",
  "lastName": "Doe",
  "email": "john.doe@example.com"
}

###

### List Accounts with Pagination (all accounts)
GET {{BankingApp.Api_HostAddress}}/api/accounts?pageNumber=1&pageSize=10
Accept: application/json

###

### List Accounts by Customer ID
GET {{BankingApp.Api_HostAddress}}/api/accounts?customerId={customerId}&pageNumber=1&pageSize=10
Accept: application/json

###

### Get Account Details
GET {{BankingApp.Api_HostAddress}}/api/accounts/{id}
Accept: application/json

###

### Get Account Balance
GET {{BankingApp.Api_HostAddress}}/api/accounts/{id}/balance
Accept: application/json

###

### Get Account Transaction History
GET {{BankingApp.Api_HostAddress}}/api/accounts/{id}/transactions?pageNumber=1&pageSize=10
Accept: application/json

###

### Create Account
POST {{BankingApp.Api_HostAddress}}/api/accounts
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "customerId": "{customerId}",
  "accountNumber": "ACC001",
  "initialBalance": 1000.00,
  "currency": "USD"
}

###

### List Transfers with Pagination (all transfers)
GET {{BankingApp.Api_HostAddress}}/api/transfers?pageNumber=1&pageSize=10
Accept: application/json

###

### List Transfers by Account ID
GET {{BankingApp.Api_HostAddress}}/api/transfers?accountId={accountId}&pageNumber=1&pageSize=10
Accept: application/json

###

### Transfer Money
POST {{BankingApp.Api_HostAddress}}/api/transfers
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "sourceAccountId": "{sourceAccountId}",
  "destinationAccountId": "{destinationAccountId}",
  "amount": 100.00,
  "reference": "Payment for services"
}
